            <title><![CDATA[Visions of Mana director Ryosuke Yoshida leaves Ouka Studios, joins Square Enix]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gematsu.com/2024/12/visions-of-mana-director-ryosuke-yoshida-leaves-ouka-studios-joins-square-enix</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/visions-of-mana-director-ryosuke-yoshida-leaves-ouka-studios-joins-square-enix.1049307/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://www.gematsu.com/2024/12/visions-of-mana-director-ryosuke-yoshida-leaves-ouka-studios-joins-square-enix<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>

    <ul>
        </ul>

    
    <p><span>"I will do my best to make a game that many people can enjoy!"</span>
      </p></div><div><p>Ryosuke Yoshida, the director of the August 29-released <em><a title="Games > Visions of Mana [13 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/visions-of-mana">Visions of Mana</a></em>, has left the <a title="Companies > NetEase Games [364 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/netease-games">NetEase Games</a>-owned developer <a title="Companies > Ouka Studios [14 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/netease-games/ouka-studios">Ouka Studios</a> and joined <a title="Companies > Square Enix [5,318 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/square-enix">Square Enix</a>, he announced. <span id="more-930632"></span></p><p>“On a personal note, I quit NetEase Ouka Studios on October 31,” Yoshida said in a <a href="https://twitter.com/YoshidaBeer/status/1863418476637118944" rel="noopener" target="_blank">tweet</a>. “We were a new studio, but we were able to release <em>Visions of Mana</em>. I am grateful to the development team and NetEase for their support. It was a very good experience. Thank you all. I am happy to announce that I joined Square Enix in December. I will do my best to make a game that many people can enjoy!”</p><p>Prior to joining Ouka Studios, Yoshida worked at <a title="Companies > Capcom [2,546 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/capcom">Capcom</a>, where he was an assistant planner on <em>Lost Planet 2</em>, a game designer on <em><a title="Series > Monster Hunter [39 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/series/monster-hunter">Monster Hunter</a>: Generations</em>, and a designer on <em><a title="Games > Devil May Cry 5 [42 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/devil-may-cry-5">Devil May Cry 5</a></em>.</p><p>(Photograph via <a href="https://www.gamespark.jp/article/2024/11/10/146813.html" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Game*Spark</a>.)</p></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
        </item>
